@* THE CONTROL (register A14, D_asyncnowrite): the template reads `msg` DIRECTLY (`@msg`), and an async
   method writes it. This already lifted to `signal('idle')` + a live effect before the S10 slice, and
   it must STAY that way -- the slice's promotion is ADDITIVE (it only ever marks MORE fields read), so
   a directly-read field is untouched. Included to prove the direct-read path does not regress. *@
<p><span id="msg">@msg</span></p>
<button id="go" @onclick="Load">go</button>

@code {
    private string msg = "idle";

    async Task Load()
    {
        await Task.Delay(1);
        msg = "done";
    }
}
